{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components"]}],"sections":[{"image":"ic_component_intro.png","title":"Use your first OUDS components","estimatedTimeInMinutes":30,"kind":"hero","chapter":"Use of first components provided by OUDS","backgroundImage":"ic_component_intro.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides components ready to be used, specified in Figma assets and preventing users to handle tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They are rendered thanks to the theme in use.","type":"text"}]}],"xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We will work on a kind of formular using main OUDS components.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Feel free to style and design things as you want.","type":"text"}]}],"mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia"}],"anchor":"Add-basic-components","title":"Add basic components","stepsSection":[{"caption":[],"code":"tutorial-3-1.swift","type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"First, prepare the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ContentView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" by adding inside it a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ScrollView"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"runtimePreview":null,"media":null},{"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add such picker with three items inside.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, let’s add radio buttons to let the user choose its gender."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The official components are "},{"code":"OUDSRadio","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"OUDSRadioItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", but the package has also a "},{"code":"OUDSRadioPicker","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to implement quicky a group of radios."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This component can be replaced by your own."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The radio picker is defined by an array of values to display radio items associated to a tag, i.e. an "},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" thing shared through a "},{"code":"Binding","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Inside a picker the user can select only one value, not zero."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-2.png","type":"step","code":"tutorial-3-2.swift"},{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a checkbox item with only two states."}]}],"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The radio picker is alone, it is the time to add below a checkbox. OUDS provides two components: ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckbox","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which is a simple checkbox, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which is a checkbox (duh!) with additional texts and icons.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The state of the checkbox is shared through a boolean ","type":"text"},{"code":"State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In some cases you may need to use ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxIndeterminate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if you want a three-states checkbox.","type":"text"}]}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-3.png","type":"step","code":"tutorial-3-3.swift"},{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Choose to add an instance of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are also components who do not have any behaviors and are here only for visual rendering, for example dividers which can be horizontal or vertical."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A divider is, in the end, a stroke with a color. You will see later, colors in OUDS have two values: a light mode value, and a dark mode value. Here the divider can have a color which can change, or not."}]}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-4.png","type":"step","code":"tutorial-3-4.swift"},{"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a switch item, it will be used as a trick to force the change of the color scheme for the view for our future operations.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You will then be able to see the automatic changes of colors when you switch the color scheme.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With radio and checkbox, OUDS provides also switch elements (toggles). They can be alone (","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwitch","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") or with texts (","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwitchItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Just like the checkbox, the switch exposes its state through a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Binding","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-5.png","type":"step","code":"tutorial-3-5.swift"},{"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add an ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSLink","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the app and make it open the iOS documentation OUDS website.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Users may need to navigate outside the app, like, for example, opening a website. Thus the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" component can be integrated. It can be only with a text or also a chevron indicator."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-6.png","type":"step","code":"tutorial-3-6.swift"},{"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s add a button with some rules: if checkbox is not checked it is disabled. When tapped, change the style of the button during 5 seconds.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the end, we can also add a button. Button are one of the most used components in an app and bring a lof of the power and the style of the brand."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can find it with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":". Such button has an appearance changing its colors, and also a style (loading or not)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Thanks to the theme, the enabled, disabled, hover, focus or pressed states are managed."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":"tutorial-3-7.png","type":"step","code":"tutorial-3-7.swift"}]}]},{"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","assessments":[{"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Does the developer using OUDS component need to manage the look and feel of the components?"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[],"type":"multiple-choice","choices":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No! The components use the design specifications, i.e. tokens, thanks to the theme, to define the style they must have in all cases."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"No","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the reason why the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is so important: it injects the theme as environment variable so that any component can get it to define its style.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"assessments"},{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Components can be similar to iOS native components, or can also be original and strongly related to Orange Unified Design System needs."}],"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","title":"Add more OUDS components","action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components"},"kind":"callToAction"}],"hierarchy":{"modules":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies","projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies"}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Preparation-of-the-theme","projects":[{"sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme#Check-Your-Understanding"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme"}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components#Add-basic-components"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-3-use-first-components#Check-Your-Understanding"}]}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Richer-and-more-original-components-of-OUDS","projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components#Add-basic-components","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-4-use-other-components"}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Typography,-view-modifiers-and-tokens","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Use-of-tokens","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Use-of-view-modifiers","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Final-result","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-5-styling-things#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}]}]},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Go-further-with-more-ressources","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-6-going-further","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-6-going-further#More-resour